Cancer Treatment Centers of America® (CTCA) has five hospitals across the United States, located in major metropolitan areas: in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, and Tulsa, Oklahoma, and near Atlanta, Georgia; Chicago, Illinois; and Phoenix, Arizona. Each of these state-of-the-art cancer centers is staffed by cancer experts who use leading-edge technologies and advanced treatments to deliver personalized, whole-person care. The CTCA® integrative treatment model treats cancer with conventional approaches like surgery, immunotherapy and chemotherapy, while also offering evidence-informed supportive therapies to manage cancer-related side effects, all under one roof.









